A debate has been raging inside the Trump administration for months over how far it will go to sanction the Iranian regime.
While the United States has withdrawn from the agreement, there remain elements of the Trump administration who view it as sacrosanct and are hoping to outlast the president.
"A nuclear Iran is the most pressing near-term threat to American national security and to the survival of our Middle East allies," Cruz said.
One senior Trump administration official, speaking only on background, told the Free Beacon that there is no good reason to issue more oil waivers.
Leading GOP lawmakers are now taking the unusual step of demanding the Trump administration stop issuing oil waivers when the current batch expires in May.